    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:38163ca9-931f-48e6-a2be-8c1b47609a48",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-description</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 39-year-old Czech male who works as a warehouse logistics coordinator in Prague. He is of medium build but appears visibly underweight and fatigued, with noticeable pallor and mild temporal wasting. He reports an unintentional weight loss of approximately 8 kg over the past four months. He has been experiencing persistent cough with occasional blood-tinged sputum, drenching night sweats, and low-grade fevers that fluctuate throughout the day [MEDDIALOG:B20.0:2].\n\n{patientName} lives alone in a two-room flat in Prague 10. He divorced three years ago and has a 10-year-old daughter whom he sees on weekends. He maintains a small circle of friends and occasionally meets them at a local pub, where he used to smoke half a pack of cigarettes daily — recently reduced due to worsening respiratory symptoms. He is a moderate social drinker.\n\nIn recent weeks, {patientName} has developed a painful lump under his left nipple as well as recurring stomach pains that prevent him from eating adequate portions, and he reports feeling immediately full upon eating [MEDDIALOG:B20.0:6]. He describes the abdominal discomfort as severe enough to limit his food intake significantly. He has also noticed spontaneous bruising on his thighs on two occasions [MEDDIALOG:B20.0:4].\n\n{patientName} enjoys cycling along the Vltava river and photography, but has been unable to pursue these hobbies over the past two months due to progressive weakness and dyspnea on exertion. He is increasingly anxious about his health and has struggled to maintain his work attendance. His employer has granted him temporary sick leave."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
